There is hereby created the Kentucky Capitol Centennial Commission, which shall be attached to the Division of Historic Properties for administrative purposes. The commission shall be composed of twenty-three (23) members, as follows:
Two (2) members of the House of Representatives, appointed by the Speaker of the House;
Two (2) members of the Senate, appointed by the President of the Senate;
The First Lady of the Commonwealth of Kentucky or her designee;
The secretary of the Economic Development Cabinet or his or her designee;
The secretary of the Tourism, Arts and Heritage Cabinet, or his or her designee;
The commissioner of the Kentucky Department of Libraries and Archives;
The director and state curator of the Division of Historic Properties;
The chairperson of the Historic Properties Advisory Commission;
The executive director of the Kentucky Arts Council;
The chairperson of the Kentucky Heritage Council;
The executive director of the Kentucky Heritage Council;
The executive director of the Kentucky Historical Society;
The president of the Kentucky Historical Society;
A representative of Kentucky State University, appointed by the president of the university;
The judge/executive of Franklin County;
The mayor of the city of Frankfort;
The executive director of the Frankfort Area Chamber of Commerce;
The executive director of the Frankfort/Franklin County Tourism Commission; and
Three (3) citizen members, one (1) of whom shall be less than thirty-five (35) years of age, from the state at large, with a demonstrated interest in Kentucky's history and substantial knowledge and appreciation of the new Capitol building, appointed by the Governor. The chair of the commission shall be elected by the members from the membership of the commission.
